                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A client admitted to the medical nursing unit has a diagnosis of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD). Metoclopramide has been prescribed 4 times a day. When would the nurse schedule administration of the medication?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nMetoclopramide is a gastrointestinal stimulant. Administration would be scheduled 30 minutes before meals and at bedtime to allow the medication time to begin working before food intake and digestion. The other options are incorrect.",
                        "id": "ba68dfe1399f47099436eb40a9f670a5",
